## Task 5: Clean validator.rs duplication ✅

**Before**: `is_path_safe` had its own inline network path checks and device path checks, duplicating the logic in `reject_network_path` and `reject_device_path`.

**After**: `is_path_safe` delegates to the shared helpers:

```rust
pub fn is_path_safe(path: &Path) -> Result<(), CiteError> {
    // Reject path traversal (..) — unique to pre-canonicalization
    for component in path.components() {
        if let std::path::Component::ParentDir = component {
            return Err(CiteError::PathRejected { ... });
        }
    }
    // Delegate to shared helpers
    reject_network_path(path)?;
    reject_device_path(path)?;
    Ok(())
}
```

This eliminates ~20 lines of duplicated path-checking logic while preserving identical behavior. All 16 validator tests pass.

